headline: 3 Services Stocks Walking a Fine Line
summary: Business services providers play a critical role for enterprises, assisting them with everything from new hardware integrations to consulting and marketing. But cutbacks in corporate spending and the threat of new AI products have kept sentiment in check, and over the past six months, the industry has tumbled by 3.5%. This drop was discouraging since the S&P 500 stood firm.
